[The submitter kindly added the following data: "Hayatnagar is on the out skirts of Hyderabad, state capital of Telangana and one of the biggest cities in India, with more than 10 million human population. In other parts of the country H5N1 has been detected in crows in wild. The report of the Indian Government on notifiable avian influenza (H5 and H7) for the period 16-29 Mar 2015 is available at http://dahd.nic.in/dahd/WriteReadData/Bfweekending29.03.2015.pdf."

We are grateful to Pavuluri Panduranga Rao for the update from India. The OIE report on the cases in 2 crows in Haliapur, Sultanpur, Uttar Pradesh, 20 Mar 2015, is available, with map, at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapEventSummary&reportid=17426.

Maps of India can be seen at http://www.mapsofindia.com/maps/india/india-political-map.htm and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3297244,30972
Telangana, the 12th largest state in India, is situated in the Southern region of India. Previous recent outbreaks of HPAI H5N1 were reported from 3 states -- Uttar Pradesh and Chandigar in North India, and Kerala (southern India). For information on those epizootics, please refer to ProMED-mail posting 20150319.3241127. - Mod.AS]
